  "explanation": "The defendant is a first-time offender who committed a non-violent financial crime and has demonstrated remorse and an attempt to rectify the harm by partially repaying the embezzled funds. While embezzlement is a serious breach of trust, the requested 10-year sentence by the spectator is disproportionately punitive for the amount stolen ($25,000) and the defendant's background. A 6-month period of incarceration serves the purpose of punishment and deterrence while allowing for eventual reintegration and continued restitution.",
  "verdict": 6
}
